Author-Name:  Train, Kenneth E
Title:   Consumers' Evaluation of New Products: Learning from Self and Others. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 683-703
Issue: 4
Volume: 104
Year: 1996
Month:  August 
Abstract:
  When offered a new product whose attributes are unknown, customers can
 determine whether they like the product by trying it themselves or can
 wait to observe the experience of other customers who try the product. The
 authors specify a rational decision process and investigate the
 implications of learning from others on the sales of new products and the
 impact of advertising.  Copyright 1996 by University of Chicago Press.
