Author-Name: Maxim Boycko
Author-Name: Andrei Shleifer
Author-Name: Natalia Tsukanova
Title:   How Does Privatization Work? Evidence from the Russian Shops. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 764-90
Issue: 4
Volume: 104
Year: 1996
Month:  August 
Abstract:
  The authors use a survey of 452 Russian shops, most of which were
 privatized between 1992 and 1993, to measure the importance of alternative
 channels through which privatization promotes restructuring. Restructuring
 is measured as major renovation, a change in suppliers, an increase in the
 hours stores stay open, and layoffs. There is strong evidence that the
 presence of new owners and new managers raises the likelihood of
 restructuring. In contrast, there is no evidence that equity incentives of
 old managers promote restructuring. The evidence points to the critical
 role new human capital plays in economic transformation.   Copyright 1996 by University of Chicago Press.
